node.text:
With the artwall created by illustrator and graphic designer @starrenco in the heart of Milan, @off____white inaugurates a global initiative in the name of female creativity, which will be unfolded through two other events around the world. Costanza's drawing, visible at Colonne di San Lorenzo for the entire month of September, takes inspiration from the unique shapes of the burrow bag, one of the most iconic items by Off-White™. 
Take a look at the video to discover how the project was born.

Credits
Talent Costanza Starrabba wearing @off____white 
Video by @maranif

node.text: "This tattoo got me into a lot of trouble because I had a contract and I wasn't supposed to get tattoos and I did; but it was worth it because I love this tattoo and the meaning behind it". Watch as British supermodel Jourdan Dunn shares the story behind her three most favourite tattoos and reveals what makes them so special.

node.title: @JourdanDunn reveals the empowering message of her tattoos

node.text:
Today we announce the 35 photographers selected for the upcoming #PhotoVogueFestival exhibition through the open call on #PhotoVogue, @Picter_com and Instagram. On Picter alone we received 24.913 images, 2.949 projects by 2.513 photographers from 98 different countries, 6 continents. 
 
Here are the selected artists: @tendercoconut_, @Alessandro.Iovino_, @BettinaPittaluga, @BryanThomasphoto, @delaliayivi, @diiegotv, @di_mathopa, @ElenaHelfrecht, @Elliott.Verdier, @FabioLasin, @Gabriele.Cecconi, @heathatrottlives, @Reanie_Beanie, @l4artiste, @jaircoll, @JodiemBateman, @Juan_Brenner, @Kaiykym, @LauraPannack, @lebo.th, @LeonardPongo, @LisandroSuriel, @Kuca_Magda, @MousLamrabat, @plantationofficial, @elriveriver, @RobertAndyCoombs2, @tondopo, @SaraBennettBrooklyn, @SilvanaTrevale, @SuleikaMueller, @Sushavan_Nandy, @africatotheworldzw, @thembinkosih15, @panremembrance. The artists have been selected by an international jury consisting of experts from across the world, with different backgrounds and vision so as to try to provide the most inclusive and multifaceted perspective. 
 
Photo Vogue Festival has always tried to challenge the danger of single, monolithic stories, and to push a multiplicity of points of view. For its 6th edition, titled “Reframing History”, we wanted to explore the projects that have reclaimed an alternative, different way of telling a tale. 
For the very first time - as part of the Reframing History scouting initiative - PVF launched a grant in collaboration with Studio RM, a prestigious creative studio with offices in London and New York, specialising in colour grading and post production for film, print and digital.
The two participants that will receive a 5,000€ cash grant each, are Lisandro Suriel and River Claure. 
 
Discover more about #VIReframingHistory at the link in bio.

node.text:
Sign of the Times: a new era for WHITE with the founder Massimiliano Bizzi and Giuseppe Angiolini, the new ambassador and art director. The project of this season includes four young promises of the Italian cinema and after the pandemic it starts again from its origins to innovate the format towards the future. Discover more! @beppe_angiolini @massimilianobizzi @whiteshowofficial @_federico_chiara_ #VogueLoves
 thanks to @superstudiogroup

node.text: For this fourth chapter of “Beauty In Storage”, Daniela Bianco and Filippo Cosmelli (@biancocosmelli), founders of @IFExperience, brought us to the Eleonora Duse’s Archive belonging to Fondazione Giorgio Cini (@fondazionegcini) in Venice. Daniela and Filippo had a conversation with Maria Ida Biggi, professor at Università Ca’ Foscari in Venice and director of Istituto per il Teatro e il Melodramma of Fondazione Giorgio Cini. Watch the video on #VogueItalia’s IGTV.

node.text:
Insieme a @WWFItalia siamo andati alla scoperta dell'Oasi WWF Le Cesine. L'Oasi si trova all'interno di un Sito d'Importanza Comunitaria nel Comune di Vernole e il suo simbolo è la beccaccia di mare.
 
La storia di questa straordinaria Oasi, in provincia di Lecce, comincia il 13 ottobre del 1939, quando viene affittata alla sezione cacciatori di Lecce. Nel 1964 per Decreto Ministeriale viene istituita la “Riserva di caccia Cesine” e negli anni successivi le mattanze ai danni della fauna si susseguono senza sosta.
 
Ma la firma della Convenzione di Ramsar nel 1971 cambia le sorti dell’area e il 1/1/1976 Le Cesine diventano un’area di tutela e rifugio per animali selvatici. Nel 1977, a seguito della ratifica della Convenzione di Ramsar avvenuta l’anno prima, l’area diviene Zona Umida di Interesse Internazionale.
 
Il paesaggio de Le Cesine è costituito da dune, area palustre, canali di bonifica, bosco misto e macchia mediterranea. Oggi l'Oasi protegge 350 ettari ed è un ambiente umido tra i meglio conservati e più importanti dell'Italia meridionale, e si trova lungo una delle principali rotte migratorie per l’avifauna e vi sono state censite circa 180 specie di uccelli. Notevolissime sono anche le presenze di anfibi, rettili e insetti.
 
A guidarci in questo viaggio Giuseppe De Matteis, Responsabile RNS Oasi Le Cesine.
 #WWFItalia

node.text:
When the vaccines made traveling further than the office possible earlier this year, @ProenzaSchouler’s #LazaroHernandez and #JackMcCollough headed straight for Kauai, a favorite destination that they call their “sanctuary.” The island vibe rubbed off on their new collection, which mixed scuba and surfing motifs, a color palette plucked from nature, and a few handmade leis from Maui with their more urban fare. Backstage after their Little Island show—the designers won the location sweepstakes this season—they clarified that Hawaii wasn’t a literal reference. But they did concede that there’s nothing as restorative as travel, especially when it comes after months of lockdown, and a year of designing garments for life at home. “They’re joyful clothes to step out in the world again.” Click the link in bio to read the review by @VogueRunway’s @NicolePhelps.
Photographed by @HunterAbrams.
#NewYorkFashionWeek

node.text:
Some things we didn’t do in the pandemic: wear 4,000 feathers head-to-toe or a stretch cashmere slip hand knit with 9,500 glass paillettes, pull on a jacket with the pneumatic sheen of a Jeff Koons sculpture, or match our shoes to our bag to our dress. #DanielLee’s latest for #BottegaVeneta is ripe with diversions. The fringed shearling coats that are this collection’s showpieces are cut in the shape of strawberries, or are they cartoon hearts? But there’s whimsy in the more everyday too; the spiral straps of high-heeled sandals were made in coordination with an actual telephone manufacturer. Lee’s clothes and accessories are reminders—lest we forget after months of lockdown and the Delta surge—of the pleasures to be found in dressing up again. 

Click the link in bio to read the review by @VogueRunway’s @NicolePhelps.

node.text: @PreciousLeexoxo closed the @CSiriano’s SS22 show at #NewYorkFashionWeek. #ChristianSiriano showed his latest collection at Gotham Hall, the former Greenwich Savings Bank. Built during the Jazz Age, the super-sized (at the time) building boasts an interior that borrows from the old world, much as American fashion leaned on Paris then. On the floor there are mosaics; high up on the wall are carved sober statements such as, “Waste neither time nor money but use both to your own good and your neighbor’s good.” The sentiment seemed strangely at odds with the lavishness of the interiors—and with Siriano’s OTT creations. node.text: #NewYorkFashionWeek skipped right back into action after an 18-month pause with @CollinaStrada’s spring 2022 show. Situated on Brooklyn Grange’s rooftop garden in Sunset Park, the show was a raucous welcome back to business as usual—although there is almost nothing usual about the way Hillary Taymour (@_collina) does business.
